The `java.awt.Rectangle` class is available to hold logical rectangles.

I reworked your code and made the following changes.

1.  I started the Swing application with a call to the `SwingUtilities` `invokeLater` method.  This method ensures that Swing components are created and executed on the [Event Dispatch Thread][1].

2.  I created and added two rectangles to a `List` of `Rectangles`.

